tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine), mild transaminitis (elevated ALT), and marked proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy with poor glycemic control. Urine is cloudy, brown, and dilute, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
